rsvp-timing
===========

This project is a derivative work. It is not an original implementation of RSVP
timing, and the attribution below is not a courtesy — the MIT license it
inherits requires it.

Origin
------

The engine originates in **rsvp-reading** by Thomas Kolmans:

    https://github.com/thomaskolmans/rsvp-reading

which is MIT licensed. The upstream module (`src/lib/rsvp-utils.js`) already
established this project's entire public surface: `getORPIndex`,
`getActualORPIndex`, `getWordDelay`, `formatTimeRemaining`,
`splitWordForDisplay`, `shouldPauseAtWord` and `extractWordFrame`.

Upstream authors of that module, by commit:

  * **Thomas Kolmans** (GitHub @thomaskolmans)
    Original implementation; multi-language support; length-calculation fixes.

  * **Egidius Mysliwietz** ("Sermak", GitHub @emysliwietz)
    "Analytic continuation of ORP Index based on word length" and
    "Word delay adjustment based on word length" — the length-sensitivity of
    both the recognition point and the per-word delay, which is the conceptual
    core of this module.

  * **adarshg** (GitHub @adarshg98765)
    Multi-word display setting (`extractWordFrame`).

Changes in this work
--------------------

Copyright (c) 2026 Benjamin Keller. Developed in the RSVP pipeline of Velo
(https://veloreader.com) and extracted here.

  * Paragraph-break handling: the `"\n"` beat token, the `"⟩"` first-word-after-
    break marker, and the reorientation pause.
  * Graduated short-word attenuation of punctuation pauses, so short words no
    longer take a full-length pause and read as a stutter.
  * Non-compounding of stacked pauses: a word that is both first-after-break and
    punctuated takes the larger of the two, not their product.
  * Trailing-noise stripping before punctuation tests, so punctuation hidden
    behind footnote markers, superscripts, closing quotes and brackets still
    registers.
  * Em-dash and en-dash treated as sentence-end-equivalent pauses, while
    compound hyphens are not.
  * Digits made ORP-countable, so numeric tokens centre like words.
  * `getORPIndex` length buckets extended to explicit 15–17 and 18+ tiers,
    replacing upstream's `Math.floor(Math.log2(len - 1)) + 1` continuation.
  * `findNearestRenderableWordIndex` and `isRenderable`.
  * The Swift implementation (`RSVPTiming.swift`) in its entirety.
  * The parity fixture and checker (`parity-vectors.json`, `generate-vectors.mjs`,
    `main.swift`).

